[[!meta title="Calculating checksums using GtkHash"]]

[<span class="application">GtkHash</span>](http://gtkhash.sourceforge.net/)
allows you to calculate [[!wikipedia checksum desc="checksums"]]. This can be
useful to verify the integrity of a file, for example, if you downloaded it from
the Internet.

To calculate the checksum of a file:

  1. Open the <span class="application">Nautilus</span> file browser, either
  from the <span class="guimenu">Places</span> menu or the <span
  class="guilabel">Computer</span> icon on the desktop.

  1. Navigate to the folder containing the file that you want to calculate the
  checksum for.

  1. Right-click on the file and choose <span class="guimenuitem">Properties</span>.

  1. In the window that pops up, activate the <span class="guilabel">Digests</span>
  tab. Check the <span class="guilabel">Hash Function</span>(s) you need and
  click the <span class="guilabel">Hash</span> button. Checksums will be
  displayer in the <span class="guilabel">Digest</span> column.
